        "question": "What kind of content works best for CPAs trying to stay visible with clients?",
        "answer": "The most effective content tends to be timely, practical, and relevant to your clients' current concerns. Tax deadline reminders, regulatory change summaries, financial planning tips tied to life events, and brief insights about industry trends all perform well. Long, technical articles tend to underperform unless your client base is specifically interested in deep financial analysis. We help you develop a content strategy that matches your clients' interests and your firm's expertise, and we make it manageable to produce consistently without it becoming a burden on your team."
