    "problemStatement": "Administrative work in a CPA firm is a death by a thousand cuts. No single admin task feels like a big deal, but the cumulative effect is staggering. Partners spend time scheduling meetings that an assistant or system could handle. Staff respond to the same client questions repeatedly because there is no self-service resource. Filing and document organization eat into production time because the system is manual or outdated. Compliance deadlines get tracked on spreadsheets that require constant manual updates. None of these tasks require CPA-level expertise, yet they consume CPA-level hours — and those are hours that could otherwise be billed to clients or spent building the practice.",
    "solutionOverview": "Saving time on admin work is not about ignoring administrative tasks — it is about making sure they do not require more time and attention than they deserve. The approach involves three layers: automating what can run without human involvement, delegating what needs human oversight but not CPA expertise, and streamlining what genuinely needs a CPA's attention so it takes less time. Each layer reduces the total administrative burden on your highest-value team members.",
