    "problemStatement": "For many tax preparers, getting paid is harder than doing the work itself. Invoices go out and then silence. Clients mean to pay but forget, or they wait until they receive their refund, or they simply do not prioritize it. The result is a cash flow pattern that looks feast-or-famine, with most revenue concentrated in a narrow window while expenses stay constant year-round. Chasing payments is also deeply uncomfortable. Nobody went into tax preparation to make collection calls, yet many firm owners spend hours each month on exactly that. The awkwardness of asking for money can even strain client relationships that were otherwise strong.",
