    "problemStatement": "Running a tax preparation practice often means juggling dozens of open returns, multiple team members, shifting deadlines, and client communications, all without a centralized way to see where things stand. Many tax preparers rely on spreadsheets, memory, or periodic manual check-ins to gauge practice performance. The result is that problems like overloaded staff, stalled returns, or revenue shortfalls only become visible after they have already caused damage. Without real time insight, managing a tax practice feels more like guesswork than strategy.",
