    "problemStatement": "Accounting firm leaders are bombarded with pitches for AI tools at every turn. Vendor demos look impressive, case studies promise dramatic results, and the fear of falling behind creates pressure to buy something, anything. But the reality inside most firms tells a different story. Many have purchased AI tools that were used enthusiastically for a week, sporadically for a month, and then quietly abandoned. Others have spent significant time evaluating options only to end up paralyzed by the sheer number of choices. The root of the problem is not a shortage of tools. It is a shortage of honest, practical guidance about which tools actually deliver in the messy reality of day-to-day accounting firm operations, and what it takes to make adoption stick.",
