    "heroDescription": "Client communication and appointment scheduling are two of the most frequent operational activities in any CPA practice, and in most firms, they operate independently of each other. A client emails a question, someone on your team responds when they get to it, and eventually a meeting gets scheduled through a separate exchange of available times. Meanwhile, proactive outreach like deadline reminders, engagement updates, and check-in messages either happens inconsistently or not at all because no one has time to manage it manually. Connecting your client communication and scheduling into a single automated system changes this dynamic entirely. Client messages trigger appropriate follow-ups and meeting invitations automatically. Appointment confirmations include relevant context from your ongoing communication history. Reminders go out before meetings and recap summaries go out after. Your clients feel like your firm is always one step ahead, and your team spends far less time coordinating the logistics that used to consume their days.",
