    "heroDescription": "For tax preparers, every return follows a similar lifecycle: collect documents, prepare the return, review it, get client approval, file it, and follow up. Multiply that by dozens or hundreds of clients and the administrative overhead becomes staggering. Task automation addresses this by handling the repetitive elements of that lifecycle automatically. Document request emails go out on schedule, status updates reach clients without manual effort, and filing checklists populate themselves based on return type. Your preparers spend their time on the technical work that requires their expertise rather than on the coordination tasks that could be systematized.",
