    "heroDescription": "In a tax preparation practice, every return involves a sequence of document-dependent steps: intake forms need to arrive before source documents can be matched, source documents need to be reviewed before preparation begins, and completed returns need to route through review before filing. When any link in that chain depends on someone remembering to move it forward, delays accumulate and deadlines get tighter. Document workflow automation connects these steps into a managed process where documents flow from intake through routing, processing, and filing with the system tracking progress and flagging exceptions. Your team stays focused on preparation and review while the workflow keeps everything moving.",
