    "heroDescription": "Accounting firms invest in software to handle specific functions: one platform for client accounting, another for document management, a third for scheduling, and perhaps a fourth for client communication. Each tool may work well on its own, but together they often create a patchwork where team members serve as the connective tissue, manually transferring data from one screen to another. Software integration addresses this by building direct pathways between your existing tools so they exchange information without human intervention. The goal is not to replace what you have but to make what you have work together as a coordinated system rather than a collection of independent applications.",
